<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<LinearLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    tools:context=".GATE"
    android:orientation="vertical"
    android:background="@drawable/login_background"
    android:padding="18dp">
    <ScrollView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:layout_weight="1">
        <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:orientation="vertical">
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="HISTORY"
                android:textColor="#FF9800"
                android:textSize="30dp"/>
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                android:textColor="@color/white"
                android:textSize="18dp"
                android:text="

*he Gateway of India is an arch monument built during the 20th century in Bombay, India. The monument was erected to commemorate the landing of King George V and Queen Mary at Apollo Bunder on their visit to India in 1911.


"/>
                 <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:textColor="@color/white"
                android:textSize="18dp"
                android:text="* Built in Indo-Saracenic style, the foundation stone for the Gateway of India was laid on 31 March 1911. The structure is an arch made of basalt, 26 metres (85 feet) high. The final design of George Wittet was sanctioned in 1914 and the construction of the monument was completed in 1924. The Gateway was later used as a symbolic ceremonial entrance to India for Viceroys and the new Governors of Bombay.  It served to allow entry and access to India.

"/>
                  <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="CONSTRUCTION"
                android:textColor="#FF9800"
                android:textSize="30dp"
                android:layout_marginTop="20dp"/>
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:textSize="18dp"
                android:textColor="@color/white"
                android:text="* The structure, in yellow basalt and concrete, is rectangular, with two long sides and two much shorter ones.
The Gateway's arch has a height of 26 metres (85 feet) with its central dome being 15 metres (49 feet) in diameter. The monument is built of yellow basalt and reinforced concrete. The stones were sourced locally while the perforated screens were brought in from Gwalior.The monument faces towards the Mumbai Harbour. There are four turrets on the structure of the gateway, and there are steps constructed behind the arch of the Gateway which lead to the Arabian Sea."/>

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="For more Information,"
                android:textColor="#FF9800"
                android:textSize="23dp"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>
            <androidx.appcompat.widget.AppCompatButton
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:id="@+id/gateinfo"
                android:text="Click here"
                android:textColor="#FFC107"
                android:textStyle="italic"
                android:background="@drawable/login_background"/>
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="Opening Time"
                android:textColor="#FF9800"
                android:textSize="24dp"/>

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text=" 	12:00 am â€“ 12:00 am"
                android:textSize="22dp"
                android:textColor="#FB5622"/>
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="The Gateway of India is open to public at all times of the day and on every day of the week. However, the most pleasant times for a visit happen to be early mornings and evenings. "
                android:textColor="@color/white"
                android:textSize="18dp"/>
            <Button
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="Special Bocking"
                android:textSize="18dp"
                android:textColor="#FFEB3B"
                android:id="@+id/gatebtn"
                android:textStyle="italic"/>

        </LinearLayout>


    </ScrollView>
</LinearLayout>